<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><p>In Andhra Pradesh, Kharif crops include Paddy (Rice), Cotton, Bajra (Pearl Millet), and Jowar (Sorghum). Rabi crops include Wheat (limited areas), Chickpea (Gram), Sunflower, and Barley. Zaid crops include Maize and Sugarcane.</p><p>Pests such as Locust and Aphids attack these crops, and pesticides like Malathion and Endosulfan are used.</p></div>
